==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mimosa
<hw>Mi*mo"sa</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ imitator. Cf. <er>Mime</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of leguminous plants, containing many species, and including the
sensitive plants (<spn>Mimosa sensitiva</spn>, and <spn>Mimosa
pudica</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term <ex>mimosa</ex> is also applied in commerce to
several kinds bark imported from Australia, and used in tanning; --
called also <altname>wattle bark</altname>.</note>
<rj><au>Tomlinson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mimosaceae</ent>⟦br⟧
